body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Deals Inc. My name is Gary Bennett. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi Gary, my name is Julie Murphy.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Julie. Can you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, three three three, one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Julie. Could you also share your email address with me?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information. I will make sure to update our records. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I'm feeling relieved now that we've sorted out the pricing issue.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that, Julie. Thank you for your time and for choosing Car Deals Inc. Have a wonderful day!
